Add NotifyKeyboardKeysym support for KDE Connect character input

KDE Connect sends character input via NotifyKeyboardKeysym (Unicode -> XKB
keysym via xkb_utf32_to_keysym). Without this method the portal returns
"No such method" for every typed character. Special keys already worked via
NotifyKeyboardKeycode.

The implementation iterates the XKB keymap to resolve keysym -> (keycode,
shift_needed) and injects the key via the existing virtual keyboard.
